1
00:00:08,291 --> 00:00:09,708
[FUBUKI]
My intention is to eliminate

2
00:00:09,791 --> 00:00:11,791
both good
and evil shinobi alike,

3
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:14,416
with this, my blade of revenge.

4
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,333
Not to mention,
this ferocious youma.

5
00:00:17,416 --> 00:00:19,833
She can't be serious.

6
00:00:19,916 --> 00:00:22,125
[RASETSU]
My name is Rasetsu.

7
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:25,833
And as Fubuki's blade, I swear
to destroy all of the shinobi.

8
00:00:25,916 --> 00:00:27,583
Whoa, just hold on.

9
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:29,500
I've never heard
a youma talk before.

10
00:00:29,583 --> 00:00:31,000
[gasps]

11
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:34,291
♪

12
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:36,000
-Guys!
-[BOTH gasp]

13
00:00:36,083 --> 00:00:37,333
[rumbling]

14
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:38,708
[gasps]

15
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:15,041
[yelling]


16
00:02:16,208 --> 00:02:17,208
[groans]


17
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:19,458
Homura, no!

18
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:22,500
[groans]

19
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:23,416
[SUZUNE]
Are you hurt?

20
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:26,083
Destroy all the shinobi?

21
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:28,375
You say that like it'll be easy.

22
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:32,750
[gasps]

23
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:34,916
[SUZUNE] Does this have to do
with Kikai Dome?

24
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Yes, the door to the other world
is about to open.

25
00:02:38,083 --> 00:02:40,000
There have been
quite a few signs.

26
00:02:40,083 --> 00:02:42,458
At long last,
everything is about to change.

27
00:02:42,541 --> 00:02:45,416
[FUBUKI]
Good and evil ninjas.

28
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:48,541
You were enemies, but now
the two sides work together

29
00:02:48,625 --> 00:02:51,666
in harmony all in the hope
of defeating the youma.

30
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:52,666
Why is that?

31
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:54,875
The reason should be obvious.

32
00:02:54,958 --> 00:02:57,041
The youma are a threat
to everything in this world,

33
00:02:57,125 --> 00:02:58,416
and that includes humanity.

34
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,375
They're a threat?

35
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:01,916
How can you be so sure?

36
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,916
Well, that's easy.

37
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,916
It's because the head shinobi
told us they were dangerous.

38
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,583
Oh, and what makes you think

39
00:03:08,666 --> 00:03:11,000
that everything
the shinobi leaders say is true?

40
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:12,000
[gasps]

41
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,500
Just shut up already!

42
00:03:13,583 --> 00:03:14,666
[grunts]

43
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,625
My mother is dead now,

44
00:03:19,708 --> 00:03:21,458
and it's all
because of the youma.

45
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:23,750
So you don't get to tell me
that they're not dangerous.

46
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:26,250
And yet you've never wondered
if the youma killed

47
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,750
by shinobi
had their own families?

48
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,500
[MIYABI]
Say what?!

49
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:34,041
It is said
that youma attack humans.

50
00:03:34,125 --> 00:03:36,291
Except, it's completely possible

51
00:03:36,375 --> 00:03:39,083
that it was the shinobi
who attacked the youma first.

52
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:40,625
Fubuki is right.

53
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:43,500
We only fought back
in order to protect ourselves.

54
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:44,958
Nonsense!

55
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:47,000
I refuse to believe such lies.

56
00:03:47,083 --> 00:03:48,125
[grunts]

57
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:49,791
♪

58
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,875
[FUBUKI]
What if I told you I had proof?

59
00:03:53,958 --> 00:03:54,916
[MIYABI]
Huh?

60
00:03:56,541 --> 00:03:57,583
[MIYABI yells]

61
00:03:58,625 --> 00:03:59,458
[MIYABI grunts]

62
00:04:01,125 --> 00:04:02,958
I can show you.

63
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:04,333
I'll prove it here and now.

64
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:06,041
[ASUKA]
That is enough!

65
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:11,333
Don't listen to anything
Fubuki says to you.

66
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:12,833
[panting]

67
00:04:12,916 --> 00:04:14,375
You've left me with no choice.

68
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:16,125
Here it goes!

69
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:19,291
I promise, I will defeat you!

70
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:22,166
Well, this is unexpected.

71
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:24,041
She still has some power.

72
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,625
It's no matter.

73
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,791
We wanted to declare war
and that's exactly what we did.

74
00:04:28,875 --> 00:04:30,916
Time to go, Rasetsu.

75
00:04:34,166 --> 00:04:35,041
Asuka.

76
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:36,916
[ASUKA gasps]

77
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,083
Hey, wait!

78
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:39,583
[SENKOU]
Lady Fubuki.

79
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:41,166
[yells]

80
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:42,125
[BOTH gasp]

81
00:04:54,416 --> 00:04:56,875
[BOTH sigh]

82
00:04:58,208 --> 00:04:59,458
[KAGURA]
Hmm.

83
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:03,750
Smile while you can.

84
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:06,458
But you won't be able to stay
on the sidelines forever.

85
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:12,208
[metallic scraping]

86
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:13,541
-Huh?
-[metallic clang]

87
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:16,916
Asuka?

88
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,333
[ASUKA]
I'm sorry, Katsuragi.

89
00:05:19,416 --> 00:05:21,666
I didn't mean to take
so long to save you.

90
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:23,708
[chuckles]
It's okay.

91
00:05:23,791 --> 00:05:26,541
But hurry, I can't grab
any boobs if I'm tied up.

92
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:27,708
-[snickers]
-[chuckles]

93
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:28,958
I'll try.

94
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:33,125
Hibari, are you in pain?

95
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:35,875
Nuh-uh. I'm fine, I promise.

96
00:05:35,958 --> 00:05:38,666
To be honest, I feel
more hungry than anything.

97
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:41,791
More importantly, are you okay?

98
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:43,708
You're looking pretty run down.

99
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:45,958
Yeah, I'm fine.

100
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:51,083
Listen, everyone.
I... I'm really--

101
00:05:51,166 --> 00:05:53,083
[KATSURAGI laughing]

102
00:05:53,166 --> 00:05:54,333
[KATSURAGI]
Aw, yeah!

103
00:05:54,416 --> 00:05:56,583
They're just as jiggly
as I remember!

104
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:00,375
Excuse you, this is not
the time for booby bongo,

105
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,625
I'm trying to say something
really important here.

106
00:06:02,708 --> 00:06:04,500
Save the love fest stuff
for later,

107
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,833
I've got a lot of fondling
to catch up on.

108
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:08,333
No more frowns, okay?

109
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:10,583
A full frontal massage
will help you relax.

110
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:12,000
[ASUKA]
No thanks!

111
00:06:12,083 --> 00:06:14,166
Cut me some slack, Asuka.

112
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:16,750
I've just been through a
traumatic experience, remember?

113
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:19,083
I need some tig
ol' bitty therapy!

114
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:21,250
Stop! This isn't the time!

115
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:22,875
-Huh?
-Seriously.

116
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:24,416
But I've waited long enough!

117
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,291
Now I'm making up for lost time!

118
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:27,541
-[laughing]
-[ASUKA groaning]

119
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:33,958
I've gotta hand it
to Katsuragi.

120
00:06:34,041 --> 00:06:37,208
She instantly went back
to normal like nothing happened.

121
00:06:37,291 --> 00:06:39,875
And she managed to lighten
the mood with her pervy antics.

122
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,833
That's true, though a bit odd.

123
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,791
[KATSURAGI] Imma squeeze
all the sadness out!

124
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:46,541
It’s all gone! So you can stop
anytime you want!

125
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:50,041
Stop, Katsuragi.
Asuka's been through enough.

126
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:52,000
Okay, but just so you know,

127
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:54,041
I'm coming after
your fun bags next!

128
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:55,333
Huh?

129
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:58,833
[IKARUGA]
Stop! Get off me, you groper!

130
00:06:58,916 --> 00:07:00,375
Come on, you know
you missed all this

131
00:07:00,458 --> 00:07:01,791
while we were knocked out.

132
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:02,916
Squeezy, squeezy!

133
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,083
Come on, you guys.

134
00:07:05,166 --> 00:07:07,666
We really don't have time
to mess around like this.

135
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:10,791
You know you're wasting
your breath, Asuka.

136
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:12,833
Katsuragi will never change.

137
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:14,458
But I think that's good.

138
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:17,416
No matter what, we need
to always be true to ourselves.

139
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,916
That way we can
each do our best.

140
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,416
You know?

141
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:23,333
[KATSURAGI] ...that means
we're dream buddies!

142
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:25,333
Uh-huh. I agree.

143
00:07:25,416 --> 00:07:26,750
-[IKARUGA grunts]
-[KATSURAGI laughs]

144
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,333
[SUZUNE]
As you may already be aware,

145
00:07:31,416 --> 00:07:34,458
there's been some suspicious
activity on Kikai Island,

146
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:35,916
where a hole has opened up.

147
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,000
[YUMI]
Yes, I saw it on the news.

148
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:42,083
That hole is actually
a door to another world.

149
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:43,541
What's more, we predicted

150
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:46,166
that a large amount
of youma would appear there.

151
00:07:46,250 --> 00:07:47,666
In preparation for that,

152
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:49,791
the shinobi leaders
deployed their jonin.

153
00:07:49,875 --> 00:07:52,625
Regardless of whether
they were good or evil,

154
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:56,083
these shinobi went to deal
with this unprecedented threat.

155
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:57,791
I see.

156
00:07:57,875 --> 00:08:01,083
Well, I suppose that explains
why Hanzo's place was closed.

157
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,291
Did Kiriya-Sensei and Daidoji

158
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:05,083
go to Kikai Island
with the others?

159
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,458
They did.

160
00:08:06,541 --> 00:08:08,791
But then,
well, after they landed

161
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:10,875
we lost all contact with them.

162
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,166
Huh?

163
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:13,375
How strange.

164
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:15,791
There's no need
to worry quite yet.

165
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:18,083
For now, we need to believe
they'll defeat the youma

166
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:20,416
and come back home
as soon as possible.

167
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:23,458
Yeah, that's true.

168
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:25,625
We'll just have to believe.

169
00:08:25,708 --> 00:08:27,125
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

170
00:08:27,208 --> 00:08:28,625
Hmm.

171
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:31,041
Anyway, back to
our other problem.

172
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:32,875
About Fubuki's proclamation.

173
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:35,125
Yes, it sounds as if
something will happen

174
00:08:35,208 --> 00:08:37,125
sooner rather than later.

175
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:38,750
I have a sneaking suspicion

176
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,416
it probably involves
a youma attack.

177
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,083
[SUZUNE]
And if it does,

178
00:08:42,166 --> 00:08:45,125
our defenses
are currently at Kikai Island.

179
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:47,166
Are you saying
that we shinobi students

180
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,166
will have to fight them
by ourselves?

181
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:51,666
Doesn't sound like
a bad deal to me.

182
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:54,791
If anything, I think it'll be
a lot of fun

183
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,583
to go head to head
with a youma.

184
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:59,875
♪

185
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:01,458
But if that's the case,

186
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:04,166
doesn't that mean we'll have to
face off against Fubuki?

187
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:06,166
[sighs]

188
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:07,708
Yes, perhaps.

189
00:09:07,791 --> 00:09:09,708
What is she doing
with the youma, though?

190
00:09:09,791 --> 00:09:10,958
-[door opens]
-Huh?

191
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:15,041
What do you think?

192
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:16,625
Will they be okay?

193
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:19,333
Who knows?
I should go check on them.

194
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:22,958
Hey, Gekkou.

195
00:09:23,041 --> 00:09:24,875
Senkou.

196
00:09:24,958 --> 00:09:26,333
Can we talk?

197
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:29,666
What is there to say?

198
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:32,583
Technically, we were
just enemies.

199
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:35,625
I know. But now, we're not.

200
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,333
Look, the thing is,
I was wondering

201
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:39,208
if you could tell us
more about Fubuki.

202
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:43,125
Well, we researched everything
we possibly could

203
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:44,958
about Master Kurokage.

204
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:46,916
And that's when we found
his records.

205
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,833
Saying he had taken
in another girl

206
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:51,166
-besides you and your friends.
-[gasps]

207
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:54,708
After that, we searched
everywhere for her.

208
00:09:54,791 --> 00:09:57,000
We were hoping that she had
inherited his beliefs

209
00:09:57,083 --> 00:09:58,666
and noble teachings.

210
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:00,125
I see.

211
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:02,166
And the girl was Fubuki.

212
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,958
That should be enough.

213
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:05,625
Besides, it's not like
there's much point

214
00:10:05,708 --> 00:10:08,125
in telling you about the Fubuki
that we trained under.

215
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:10,958
Obviously the Fubuki
we know is long gone.

216
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:12,541
[gasps]

217
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:21,125
♪

218
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:26,125
♪

219
00:10:27,541 --> 00:10:30,416
[owl hooting]

220
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:33,875
Do you remember the last time
we walked together like this?

221
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:36,458
I do. Like it was yesterday.

222
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:40,958
♪

223
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,541
[GEKKOU gasps]
Are you...

224
00:10:50,625 --> 00:10:52,208
Could you be?

225
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:55,708
You may call me Fubuki.

226
00:10:55,791 --> 00:10:57,375
I knew it.

227
00:10:57,458 --> 00:11:00,208
[FUBUKI] Why have
the two of you come here?

228
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:04,125
[SENKOU] Can you please tell us
about Master Kurokage?

229
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:05,333
[GEKKOU]
We read about him,

230
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:07,750
and we wanna
carry on his beliefs.

231
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:09,041
Please.

232
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:10,583
I see. All right.

233
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:14,375
In that case, I think we have
a lot to talk about.

234
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:17,375
♪

235
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:21,458
[GEKKOU] We learned what path
we needed to follow

236
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:24,333
because of Master Kurokage
and Lady Fubuki.

237
00:11:24,416 --> 00:11:25,875
But now,

238
00:11:25,958 --> 00:11:28,333
I guess we're not any different
than this waterfall.

239
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:33,500
Racing toward an end
with no future in sight.

240
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,750
What are we supposed to do?

241
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:41,125
We could always try going back
to the life we had before.

242
00:11:41,208 --> 00:11:42,916
Back to those empty days.

243
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,041
I can't handle that.

244
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:46,333
Neither can I.

245
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:50,083
Then I guess... That means...

246
00:11:50,166 --> 00:11:53,541
♪

247
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:56,625
[YUMI] I need to find them
before it's too late.

248
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,375
-Gekkou! Senkou!
-[BOTH] Huh?

249
00:12:04,416 --> 00:12:06,625
Please, you don't
have to do this.

250
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:10,250
We don't want to see you,
just go away.

251
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:12,333
Kurokage's beliefs
were all a lie.

252
00:12:12,416 --> 00:12:14,666
Then Fubuki betrayed us.

253
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:17,333
We've lost our only sense
of purpose.

254
00:12:17,416 --> 00:12:19,583
[YUMI]
Lost beliefs, betrayal?

255
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:22,583
Are those things
really worth dying for?

256
00:12:22,666 --> 00:12:25,125
You have no idea
what we're going through.

257
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:27,583
True. I don't know.

258
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:31,875
Because my experiences have
been very different from yours.

259
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:33,875
So keep quiet, then.

260
00:12:33,958 --> 00:12:35,833
[GEKKOU]
Please leave us alone.

261
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,583
All I want is to
talk with you two.

262
00:12:40,666 --> 00:12:41,833
[SENKOU]
Talk?

263
00:12:41,916 --> 00:12:43,666
Yes, If you don't mind.

264
00:12:43,750 --> 00:12:45,291
I thought maybe you would like
to hear more

265
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:46,666
about my grandfather.

266
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,583
Particularly,
his sense of justice.

267
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:50,875
There's nothing left to say.

268
00:12:50,958 --> 00:12:53,375
We already know we were wrong,
so what else is there?

269
00:12:53,458 --> 00:12:57,208
It's obvious we didn't know
Master Kurokage the way you did.

270
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:59,458
His true sense of justice

271
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:01,625
is something we could
never understand.

272
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:03,916
Hmm. Well, I believe in you.

273
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,583
I have faith you'll come
to understand it just fine.

274
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:10,958
[SENKOU gasps]

275
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:13,125
I'm sorry.

276
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:15,958
It's freezing,
my hand must be cold.

277
00:13:16,041 --> 00:13:18,666
It's not.
I'm actually surprised.

278
00:13:19,916 --> 00:13:22,416
Your hand is warm.

279
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,416
[YUMI]
I see. Then I'm glad.

280
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:28,625
This is something I learned
from Grandfather Kurokage.

281
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,416
That was his justice.

282
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:34,583
Warmth is important.
It's precious.

283
00:13:35,708 --> 00:13:39,041
Justice exists to protect
those you love.

284
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:42,041
[inaudible]

285
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:45,666
[YUMI]
Can you understand how I feel?

286
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:48,750
And how
Grandfather Kurokage felt?

287
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:51,166
[GEKKOU sobbing quietly]

288
00:13:52,208 --> 00:13:53,250
[GEKKOU]
Yes.

289
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,208
♪

290
00:13:58,291 --> 00:14:01,041
Well, that takes care
of Gekkou and Senkou.

291
00:14:01,125 --> 00:14:02,583
They'll be fine, right?

292
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:05,416
I hope, but I'm still
a little worried.

293
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,666
I think maybe
they should go stay

294
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,333
with Ikaruga and the others.

295
00:14:08,416 --> 00:14:11,208
Would you mind telling them
for me, Homura?

296
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,000
Hold on.
Where do you think you're going?

297
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:18,500
Ikaruga is your friend,
why don't you tell her yourself?

298
00:14:18,583 --> 00:14:20,958
And there's still a lot of stuff
that we need to talk about.

299
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:23,541
-For starters--
-[ASUKA] Homura.

300
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,541
You said that
if I defeated you,

301
00:14:26,625 --> 00:14:28,958
then you'd accept
my feelings, remember?

302
00:14:29,041 --> 00:14:30,000
[HOMURA]
Yeah. I do.

303
00:14:30,083 --> 00:14:31,916
[ASUKA]
Okay.

304
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,000
I need to do this.

305
00:14:34,083 --> 00:14:37,000
I have to follow the path
of the shinobi to its end.

306
00:14:37,083 --> 00:14:39,416
What does that mean?

307
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:40,541
Hey, Asuka!

308
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:44,625
What the heck
is she even talking about?

309
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:50,333
[HIBARI] So, what do you guys
wanna do for lunch?

310
00:14:50,416 --> 00:14:53,708
We have to stay put until
Suzune-Sensei gives us orders.

311
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:55,250
We're not allowed to go out.

312
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:58,708
In that case,
sounds like it's ramen time!

313
00:14:58,791 --> 00:15:00,833
Where did those come from?

314
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:03,041
And why can't we go eat
in the cafeteria?

315
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:04,833
Why would you want to?

316
00:15:04,916 --> 00:15:08,000
They don't even have ramen cups
down there, just normal food.

317
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:10,541
[YAGYU] Jeez. What's with
this ramen obsession?

318
00:15:10,625 --> 00:15:12,250
[IKARUGA] What about you,
Gekkou and Senkou,

319
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:13,875
what would you like to eat?

320
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:15,625
[GEKKOU gasps]

321
00:15:15,708 --> 00:15:17,333
I don't care.

322
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:19,041
It doesn't matter.

323
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:21,708
Awesome, then instant ramen
is the winner!

324
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:25,541
Okay, there's Tonkotsu,
soy sauce, miso, niboshi, iekei.

325
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:27,625
You name it, I've got it!

326
00:15:27,708 --> 00:15:29,333
And for dessert...

327
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:31,875
-[IKARUGA gasps]
-we can have some melons!

328
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:33,666
Cut it out, Katsuragi!

329
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:35,083
I can't help it!

330
00:15:35,166 --> 00:15:36,333
They're so soft.

331
00:15:36,416 --> 00:15:37,541
I gotta squeeze 'em.

332
00:15:37,625 --> 00:15:38,791
[KATSURAGI laughing]

333
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:41,583
Squeezy, squeezy, squeeze!

334
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:43,958
Stop or I swear I'll end you!

335
00:15:44,041 --> 00:15:45,083
[KATSURAGI shrieks]

336
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:49,541
Here. This is
a squid flavored ramen.

337
00:15:49,625 --> 00:15:50,958
It's the best.

338
00:15:51,041 --> 00:15:52,500
[BOTH groan]

339
00:15:53,541 --> 00:15:55,041
[slurping]

340
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,583
Hey. So, uh...

341
00:16:00,666 --> 00:16:02,458
Yes, did you need
something, Gekkou?

342
00:16:03,583 --> 00:16:05,458
Aren't you still mad at us?

343
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:07,958
You know, for all of the things
we did to you?

344
00:16:08,041 --> 00:16:11,958
You mean when you kidnapped us
and tied us up?

345
00:16:12,041 --> 00:16:13,875
-[BOTH sigh]
-Yeah, that.

346
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,458
Yeah, of course I'm mad.

347
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:19,791
[BOTH sigh]

348
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,375
[KATSURAGI]
I'm mad at myself.

349
00:16:21,458 --> 00:16:22,958
For losing to you.

350
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:24,375
[BOTH]
Huh?

351
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:27,208
You caught us by surprise
but that's no excuse.

352
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:30,000
We should've been more prepared,
so no hard feelings.

353
00:16:30,083 --> 00:16:32,000
Hey, your ramen's gonna
get soggy.

354
00:16:32,083 --> 00:16:33,458
You'd better eat it quickly.

355
00:16:33,541 --> 00:16:34,875
Uh, okay.

356
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:39,166
We'll practice more
and get even stronger.

357
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:41,500
And then maybe we can fight
again someday.

358
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:44,791
If we ever have a rematch
with them, I'll definitely win.

359
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,000
If you want me to prove it,

360
00:16:46,083 --> 00:16:47,833
I'd be willing
to fight right now.

361
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:50,666
Hold on, you shouldn't say
things like that, Yagyu.

362
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:53,583
If you act mean, I won't wanna
be friends with you anymore.

363
00:16:53,666 --> 00:16:54,958
-Hmph.
-Seriously?

364
00:16:55,041 --> 00:16:57,208
If you're joking, Hibari,
it's not very funny.

365
00:16:57,291 --> 00:16:59,333
You didn't really mean
any of those things, did you?

366
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:00,250
Be honest.

367
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:01,416
I did.

368
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,458
Unless you say to Gekkou
and Senkou,

369
00:17:03,541 --> 00:17:05,750
"Let's all be friends
and do our best together."

370
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,833
[gasping]

371
00:17:09,583 --> 00:17:12,333
Let's all be friends
and do our best together.

372
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:14,125
Right.

373
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,250
Uh... Hey.

374
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:19,625
Awesome,
now that we're all friends,

375
00:17:19,708 --> 00:17:21,166
you can relax a little!

376
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:23,625
-[laughing]
-Let go of me.

377
00:17:23,708 --> 00:17:24,833
Cut it out!

378
00:17:24,916 --> 00:17:26,625
[KATSURAGI]
We have to come together,

379
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:27,958
or we'll never defeat the youma.

380
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:30,125
This is the best way to bond!

381
00:17:30,208 --> 00:17:31,458
-There ya go!
-Stop it!

382
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:33,333
This position is much better,
am I right?

383
00:17:35,166 --> 00:17:36,791
We can't come together yet.

384
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:39,041
Because we're missing
someone very important.

385
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:41,291
Are you talking about Asuka?

386
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:45,333
We haven't heard anything
from her yet, have we?

387
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:50,500
♪

388
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:51,958
-[GEKKOU gasps]
-[KATSURAGI chuckles]

389
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,333
Come on, didn't I tell you guys

390
00:17:53,416 --> 00:17:55,083
that you need to relax
a little bit?

391
00:17:55,166 --> 00:17:56,416
Help, Senkou!

392
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,458
Please. Get her off of me!

393
00:17:58,541 --> 00:17:59,916
[SENKOU]
Unhand my sister!

394
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,083
Let her go!

395
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:02,583
[gasps]

396
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:04,458
-[sobbing]
-I...

397
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:06,083
Uh... I'm sorry.

398
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:07,583
Nice job, Senkou!

399
00:18:07,666 --> 00:18:08,833
[SENKOU]
Shut up!

400
00:18:08,916 --> 00:18:10,166
That's enough.

401
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:13,333
I can't handle your perversity
right now.

402
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:15,875
Why aren't we out
looking for Asuka?

403
00:18:15,958 --> 00:18:17,833
Aren't you guys worried
about her?

404
00:18:17,916 --> 00:18:19,041
Hmm.

405
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:23,625
No, I'm sure Asuka
probably just has something

406
00:18:23,708 --> 00:18:25,291
she needs to handle herself.

407
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:27,666
And once she's finished
with whatever it is,

408
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,791
I'm sure that she'll
come back home to us.

409
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,916
We just need to believe in her.

410
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,375
Believe in her?

411
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:38,416
Yeah, pretty much.

412
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:41,833
I think it's the best we can do
for Asuka right now.

413
00:18:49,541 --> 00:18:51,208
Hello, Asuka.

414
00:18:51,291 --> 00:18:53,083
Is Kagura here?

415
00:18:53,166 --> 00:18:54,583
She's busy.

416
00:18:54,666 --> 00:18:57,333
Kagura is storing her power
for the upcoming battle.

417
00:18:57,416 --> 00:18:59,458
I can't allow anyone
to see her right now.

418
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:02,833
Hold on.

419
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:05,500
Kagura has already given you
a portion of her power.

420
00:19:05,583 --> 00:19:07,708
What more do you want from her?

421
00:19:07,791 --> 00:19:09,500
[ASUKA]
I just need to talk to her.

422
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:14,791
[NARAKU] Don't tell me you
intend to use what she gave you.

423
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:16,625
That's been my plan
from the start.

424
00:19:18,083 --> 00:19:20,125
I see. Kagura.

425
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:22,333
Kagura.

426
00:19:22,416 --> 00:19:23,208
[rustling]

427
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:24,625
[KAGURA]
Coming!

428
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,625
Hi, Asuka.

429
00:19:28,708 --> 00:19:30,333
Did you need somethin' from me?

430
00:19:30,416 --> 00:19:32,708
I want you
to promise me something.

431
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:35,333
I need you to let me
handle the youma.

432
00:19:35,416 --> 00:19:36,875
A promise, huh?

433
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:39,583
Sorry, but you know
I can't agree to that.

434
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:42,083
Because beating youma
is my responsibility.

435
00:19:42,166 --> 00:19:43,375
Just say it!

436
00:19:43,458 --> 00:19:45,583
Don't be rude, Asuka.

437
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:48,583
That's the second time
you've looked at me that way.

438
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:54,125
[KAGURA] You want to seal
the youma without killing them?

439
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:57,625
You do know a way
to do it, don't you, Kagura?

440
00:19:57,708 --> 00:19:59,166
Yeah, of course I do.

441
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:01,125
But why do you want
to seal them away?

442
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:04,125
It'd probably be easier
to just beat them.

443
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,125
I need another way.

444
00:20:06,208 --> 00:20:07,666
You do, huh?

445
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:10,083
You must have
a pretty good reason.

446
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:11,125
Okay.

447
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:13,000
I'll tell you how to do it.

448
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,416
If you're that determined,

449
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,000
I guess I can
leave you in charge.

450
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:18,583
Wait, Kagura.

451
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:21,500
Although, you haven't
actually sealed

452
00:20:21,583 --> 00:20:23,500
a youma by yourself, have you?

453
00:20:23,583 --> 00:20:25,500
Can you get it right
on your first try?

454
00:20:25,583 --> 00:20:28,000
I'll be just fine.

455
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:30,250
[KAGURA]
Maybe you should do a test run.

456
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:33,750
I'll open a small door
to the other world.

457
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,541
-[YOUMA roaring]
-[ASUKA gasps]

458
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:39,958
Super-Secret Ninja Art:

459
00:20:40,041 --> 00:20:42,250
Go! Fuma Korin!

460
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:51,541
Excellent work, Asuka.

461
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,791
But don't forget
the most important thing.

462
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:56,833
If you keep using
that Super-Secret Art,

463
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:58,375
you'll eventually die.

464
00:21:04,583 --> 00:21:06,125
[groans]

465
00:21:06,208 --> 00:21:09,791
If I have to die,
that's what I'll do.

466
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,791
[WOMAN]
Is that bear your friend?

467
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:13,291
[GIRL]
Yeah, we're always together.

468
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:14,833
[BOTH laugh]

469
00:21:14,916 --> 00:21:17,666
[WOMAN] Well, then you need
to take good care of him.

470
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:27,125
♪

471
00:21:27,208 --> 00:21:29,000
[FUBUKI]
The islands of Japan and Kikai

472
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:31,125
are connected by a ley line,

473
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:32,958
which means one thing.

474
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:36,833
The door to the other world
must also be connected.

475
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:40,125
♪

476
00:21:45,916 --> 00:21:48,583
Now, it's time to begin.

477
00:21:51,250 --> 00:21:53,041
[MINORI]
Yumi. Come here, hurry!

478
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:57,125
♪

479
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,416
Yumi, those are...

480
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,166
[YUMI gasps]

481
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:37,208
Hmm-mm! [gasps]

482
00:23:37,291 --> 00:23:38,875
I don't have any feelings,

483
00:23:38,958 --> 00:23:40,750
so I don't know
what the big deal is.

484
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:43,583
Yeah, me either.
It doesn't bother me at all.

485
00:23:43,666 --> 00:23:45,166
You're only saying that
because you have

486
00:23:45,250 --> 00:23:47,166
ginormous watermelon tits,
you big braggart.

487
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:48,250
[chuckles]

